history.text: Hi. Did you like this movie?
Hi, I like the actors in this movie but I didn't like the movie much. How about you?
I liked the actor playing Lex Luthor but not Batman.
I thought Wonder Woman was the best aspect of the movie.
I can agree with that, I really like Gal Gadot
I haven't heard of the actor playing Lex Luthor
I thought he brought a new-age tech-iness to the villian.
Superman to me is pretty ageless... too goodie two-shoe and boring.
That definitely sounds interesting about Luthor, and yeah I generally prefer Marvel heroes
I'm most familiar with those characters and movies
I think the Critic's response is rather funny... as I do agee marvel movies tend to just advertise their own product.
Yeah I liked the critical reviews too, I think they're funny. They seem pretty harsh in regards to cohesiveness of the plot.
I also don't get why it too Superman 18 years to decide he didn't like Batman and to do something about it... being the plot of this movie.
It is easy to understand why humans dislike superman and his species as they wrecked havoc on earth pretty quick.
Yeah that's a good point. Also it seems to me that a fight between batman and Superman would be pretty skewed in Superman's favor realistically
Yeah but batman has to represent technology and money.
That's true, do you think he could be representative of societal and governmental resistance to superman?
Possibly. Wonder what is the symbolism of both their mothers being named Martha.
I didn't even notice that at first, that is an interesting point. Seems like it must not be coincidence
Emphasizes they both put themselves first before realizing that Lex Luthor is playing them both.
I'm glad they teamed up together but I still dont really see why Superman dislikes Batman so much.
I don't see why either, it just says Superman dislikes Batman's "form of justice."
I'm not entirely sure what that means and it seems like the two have pretty similar goals
Perhaps it is because he's a vigilante and hides his identity. But then so does superman... and all it takes for him is a pair of glasses for some reason.
At least batman feels bad about how poorly relations went with Superman. Too bad Superman had to die.
Yeah true, maybe he sees Batman as too brutal or extreme? I'm really not sure why he'd feel the way he did
Yeah Batman seems like he might have the better conscience here
I like that the soil on his coffin levitates. You know Superman isn't dead!
Yeah that's a fun detail, definitely leaves the story open to continuation, or at least lots of fun questions for viewers
Do you know if wonder woman will help Bruce form the team of meta humans to protect earth?
I could definitely see that happening, I think Wonder Woman might be detached enough from the conflict to see that as most beneficial
I think this movie deserved more than the 27% rotten tomatoes score. I didnt read any comics but I thought it was at least a fun movie desrving of more positive review.
I thought the review was pretty harsh too. I think Rotten Tomatoes especially tends to be pretty extreme with ratings.I agree, I've seen better superhero movies but this one was entertaining enough
I am curious what alien threats might come while Superman is dead. And which metahumans will choose to help Batman.

That is interesting, and I wonder if 
their might be a sort of power void that'll be filled with superman gone. Not that he was anyone's leader necessarily but he's obviously a powerful figure
And if any meta humans sympathetic to superman would refuse to help Batman
That's a good point. I wonder who else dislikes Batman's justice?
True true, I'm sure superman isn't alone in that
I know nothing of the comics and am excited to see where the story goes!
I wonder if Superman will become bad? Like if he is risen from the dead. Zombie Superman?
That could be a really interesting twist! Maybe Luthor or another villain might even try to use whatever superman becomes as a weapon for their cause
I would hope Superman's grave isn't easily accessible!
Yes hopefully not!
